    "minides": "India's most trusted workhorse — the Bolero facelift brings modern features to a proven 7-seat body-on-frame SUV under ₹10 lakh.",
    "description": "The 2025 Mahindra Bolero facelift was launched on 6 October 2025, starting at ₹7.99 lakh (ex-showroom). It is offered in four variants — B4, B6, B6(O), and B8 — all powered by the 1.5-litre mHawk75 3-cylinder turbo-diesel producing 75 bhp and 210 Nm, paired with a 5-speed manual gearbox and rear-wheel drive. The updated Bolero measures under 4 metres (3,995 mm), qualifying for lower GST. Key updates include RideFlo suspension technology, a new 7-inch touchscreen on B6 and above, steering-mounted controls, digital instrument cluster, USB Type-C charging, leatherette upholstery on B8, diamond-cut alloy wheels on B8, fog lamps on B6(O) and B8, and a new Stealth Black colour option. All variants seat 7 in a 5+2 layout and include dual airbags, ABS with EBD, and rear parking sensors as standard. The 2025 prices are up to ₹80,000 lower than the pre-facelift model."
  },
